{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 12:56:54.696416", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary of Network Health\\n- Data-plane connectivity is fully degraded. All host-to-host pings fail, including between hosts on the same leaf.\\n- Control-plane connectivity to the SDN controller IP (20.0.0.100) is reachable at the IP layer (ICMP OK from all switches), but OpenFlow connections from all OVS bridges are refused by the controller. As a result, the fabric has no forwarding entries and drops all traffic due to fail_mode=secure on each switch.\\n- Physical/data interfaces appear up (LIVE) on all OVS devices, with no link errors observed.\\n\\nEvidence and Findings\\n\\n1) Reachability tests (ICMP)\\n- host_1_1 -> host_1_2: 100% loss with “Destination Host Unreachable”.\\n- host_2_1 -> host_2_2: 100% loss with “Destination Host Unreachable”.\\n- Cross-leaf pings (e.g., host_1_1 -> host_2_1) also fail 100% with the same error.\\nInterpretation: Even same-subnet pairs cannot communicate, indicating L2 switching/forwarding is not functioning. ARP likely not being forwarded/answered.\\n\\n2) OVS controller status and flow tables\\n- All switches configured with Controller \"tcp:20.0.0.100:6633\" and fail_mode: secure.\\n- Controller connection state on leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1:\\n  - is_connected: false\\n  - status: last_error=\"Connection refused\", state=BACKOFF\\n- ICMP to controller:\\n  - leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1 can ping 20.0.0.100 successfully (low latency, 0% loss).\\n- Flow tables:\\n  - ovs-ofctl dump-flows on leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1: empty (no flows installed).\\n- Port status:\\n  - ovs-ofctl show indicates eth0/eth1/eth2 on all switches are LIVE; no evidence of port-down events on the data interfaces. LOCAL ports show LINK_DOWN (expected for the local pseudo-port), not indicating a data-plane issue.\\n\\n3) Host and switch interface/IP configuration\\n- Hosts host_1_1 (10.0.0.1/24), host_1_2 (10.0.0.2/24), host_2_1 (10.0.0.3/24), host_2_2 (10.0.0.4/24) have correct IPs, interfaces UP.\\n- Switch management interfaces are in 20.0.0.0/24 and can reach 20.0.0.100.\\n- No abnormal interface errors/drops reported on the data ports.\\n\\nAnomalies Detected\\n- Global OpenFlow control-plane failure: All OVS bridges cannot establish an OpenFlow session to 20.0.0.100:6633; connections are refused.\\n- Absence of any OpenFlow rules on the switches combined with fail_mode=secure causes total data-plane drop, explaining complete host-to-host unreachability (including intra-leaf pairs).\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Primary faulty component: The SDN controller at 20.0.0.100 (or its OpenFlow service) is not accepting connections on TCP port 6633. Since ICMP to 20.0.0.100 succeeds, this is not a network reachability issue but a service/port-level issue (no listener or wrong port).\\n- Affected devices: All OVS switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) are impacted as downstream victims due to fail_mode=secure and lack of controller-delivered flows, but they are not the root cause.\\n\\nRoot Cause Assessment\\n- The controller process is either down, misconfigured, or listening on a different port than 6633, leading to “Connection refused” for OpenFlow sessions from all switches.\\n- Because each OVS bridge is configured with fail_mode=secure and has no flows installed, the fabric drops all traffic, causing all host connectivity to fail.\\n\\nImpact\\n- Complete service outage across the fabric: intra-leaf, inter-leaf, and end-to-end traffic is dropped.\\n- Management plane is intact (switches can ping the controller IP), but control plane (OpenFlow TCP session) is unavailable., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='cd96763a-d7f6-44ef-bf4a-f1bfbec39f3e'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
